Architecture plan for issues #97 and #98

Project shape
- Next.js App Router frontend in src/app with React/TypeScript components in src/components.
- Public homepage is src/app/(public)/page.tsx and uses Prisma server-side reads for latest posts/subspaces/tags.
- Header/navigation is src/components/site-header.tsx with session controls delegated to src/components/session-controls.tsx.
- Styling is Tailwind via src/app/globals.css and existing design tokens/classes.

Issue #97: Simplify homepage hero/latest posts
- Update src/app/(public)/page.tsx only unless tests require small helper adjustments.
- Preserve public data fetching and post card rendering, but change LATEST_POST_LIMIT from 10 to 20.
- Replace the current hero copy/buttons with a single h1: "The Lastest Global AI News" exactly as specified, preserving the misspelling.
- Remove the browse subspaces/tags CTA buttons and their wrapper from the homepage hero.
- Keep JSON-LD, metadata, latest-posts section behavior, and existing link destinations in post/subspace/tag content.

Issue #98: Active top-nav item
- Convert src/components/site-header.tsx to a client component with "use client" and usePathname from next/navigation.
- Keep SessionControls rendered as-is.
- Add small local helper logic to classify active routes:
  - Subspaces active on /subspaces and /s/*.
  - Tags active on /tags and /t/*.
- Apply filled accent styling to the active link and muted styling to inactive links using existing Tailwind color tokens.
- Preserve hrefs and accessible nav structure.

Dependencies and sequencing
- Issue #98 depends on the header remaining present across all pages but does not depend on Issue #97 implementation details.
- Issue #97 can be completed independently first; Issue #98 can follow without touching homepage internals.
- Shared risk: header is a server component today; making it client-side should avoid server-only imports in that file. SessionControls is already client-side and safe to compose.

Validation plan
- Run npm run typecheck and npm test when dependencies are available.
- For UI changes, verify homepage root, /subspaces, /s/* route matching if data exists, /tags, and /t/* route matching if data exists.
- Confirm the homepage still renders styled content and the signed-out auth UI remains coherent.
